    "about": {
      "title": "About me",
      "description": "I'm Francisco — a <strong class=\"font-bold\">Senior Fullstack Engineer</strong> from Monterrey, Mexico, now living in The Woodlands, Texas, fully authorized to work in the United States.<br><br>I don't just write code. I think in systems, user flows, and business impact. While most engineers focus on features, I focus on outcomes: how the system scales, how users experience it, and how the team maintains it over time.<br><br>I specialize in <strong class=\"font-bold text-red-400 dark:text-red-300\">Angular</strong>, <strong class=\"font-bold text-blue-400 dark:text-blue-300\">React</strong>, and <strong class=\"font-bold text-green-400 dark:text-green-300\">Node.js</strong>, with deep experience in frontend architecture, performance optimization, and testing — primarily inside monorepos. I've shipped enterprise solutions for global brands like <strong class=\"font-bold\">Royal Caribbean</strong>, <strong class=\"font-bold\">United Airlines</strong>, and <strong class=\"font-bold\">Dick's Sporting Goods</strong>. My <strong class=\"font-bold\">GitHub</strong> and side projects are proof, not promises.<br><br>I've also been integrating <strong class=\"font-bold\">AI</strong> into my workflow in a pragmatic way — using it to accelerate development, explore solutions, and increase iteration speed, while making intentional decisions about when and how to apply it. Not chasing hype. Building leverage.<br><br>Currently building <strong class=\"font-bold\">Kindnest</strong>, a community management platform with payment architecture and admin systems, and internal tooling to generate landing pages and automate client workflows with AI-assisted development.<br><br>Core strengths: frontend architecture &amp; scalable systems, performance &amp; accessibility (WCAG), testing (Jest, Cypress), AI-assisted development, and product thinking.<br><br>I don't just build components. I build systems that let teams ship faster without losing quality."
    }
  },
